Boris Johnson's controversial bill to override post-Brexit rules on Northern Ireland has been dropped by Prime Minister Rishi Sunak after he negotiated a new deal with the European Union. In turn, Brussels has agreed to scrap its legal action against Britain. This was launched in retaliation against the former prime minister's Northern Ireland Protocol Bill.  Mr Johnson had warned his successor that scrapping the bill would be a "great mistake". But the Government's new Windsor Framework, finalised with European Commission president Ursula von der Leyen on Monday, said it was no longer needed. It reads: "The Government will therefore not be proceeding with the Northern Ireland Protocol Bill."  FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES: